narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you got to take it, take it. But if you're just trying to learn the language, do a summer abroad or something.
Yes I would recommend it to another student, its not too much of a step up from L2, but you continue to tune your writing and speaking skills.

Want to learn spanish? This is a great way to do it. Readings, discussion, movies are interesting and the book clear. You really have to do ALL the work ON time and attend the classes ON time, which makes it a heavy, but steady workload throughout the semester. You really feel you can use the language after taking this course.
